      <section class="card">
        <h2 style="color:var(--accent);margin-top:0">Design Philosophy</h2>
        <p style="margin:0 0 10px" class="muted">Goals, choices, and reasoning that guided the site design</p>
        <ol>
          <li><strong>Clarity & focus:</strong> Prioritise readable content hierarchy — clear headings, concise copy, and generous spacing so users (and instructors) can scan quickly.</li>
          <li><strong>Accessible aesthetics:</strong> Use high contrast (brand red #be0909 against white) and large hit targets. All images will include alt text and semantic HTML will be used for structure.</li>
          <li><strong>Performance-first:</strong> Minimal dependencies and compressed assets so the site loads fast on limited connections.</li>
          <li><strong>Consistent system:</strong> A single set of design tokens (colors, radii, type scale) keeps the site visually consistent — this hidden page pulls the same <code>--brand-red</code> token as the public site.</li>
          <li><strong>Mobile-first responsiveness:</strong> Grid and flexible spacing ensure the site works well on phones and tablets.</li>
        </ol>
        <p class="muted" style="margin-top:8px">Reasoning: these choices make the product approachable for prospective users while keeping implementation simple for student teams to maintain.</p>
      </section>

      <section class="card">
